data.title: Prime Ministers of New Zealand since 1856
data.text:
Please note that the term Premier was used until 1899.

Prior to self-government there were two “unofficial ministries” led by James FitzGerald (14 June to 2 August 1854) and Thomas Forsaith (31 August to 2 September 1854). They were neither Premiers nor Colonial Secretaries.

You can find more detail on all MPs in the Roll of members of the NZ House of Representatives, 1854 onwards.

[1] There were no political parties before 1890

[2] Frederick Whitaker was a member of the Legislative Council and a member of the House of Representatives at different times. Both his terms as Premier were while he was a member of the Legislative Council.

[3] George Waterhouse was a member of the Legislative Council

[4] Daniel Pollen was a member of the Legislative Council
